Banyan Breast Cancer Analysis

Carter Allen

11/12/2021

Load Packages

# packages
library(Seurat)
library(banyan)
library(tidyverse)

Load Data

We will consider the Invasive Ductal Carcinoma breast tissue from BioIVT Asterand sequenced with the 10X Visium platform and made publicly available by (10X Genomics)[https://support.10xgenomics.com/spatial-gene-expression/datasets/1.0.0/V1_Breast_Cancer_Block_A_Section_1]. We will create a Seurat object using the raw expression count matrix and spatial coordinates files.

# read data
# expression counts
exp <- data.table::fread(paste0(data_dir,"SGE1.1.0_humanBreastCancer_expression_den.csv"))
spots <- c(exp[,1])[[1]]
exp <- as.matrix(exp[,-1])
rownames(exp) <- spots

# cell spot coordinates
metadata <- data.table::fread(paste0(data_dir,"SGE1.1.0_humanBreastCancer_metaData.csv")) 
coords <- metadata %>%
  select(array_row,array_col)
rownames(coords) <- metadata$barcode

Pre-Process Data

breast <- CreateSeuratObject(counts = t(exp), assay = "Spatial")
breast@images$image = new(Class = "SlideSeq",
                          assay = "Spatial",
                          key = "image_",
                          coordinates = coords)
breast <- SCTransform(breast, assay = "Spatial", verbose = FALSE)
breast <- RunPCA(breast, assay = "SCT", verbose = FALSE)

Fit Model

# fit banyan
breast_fit <- fit_banyan(seurat_obj = breast, K = 5)

Plot Results

# plot labels
plot_labels(breast_fit)

# calculate scores
breast_fit <- get_scores(breast_fit)
# plot uncertainty
plot_uncertainty(breast_fit)

# plot propensity
plot_propensity(breast_fit,k = 1) + plot_propensity(breast_fit,k = 2)

# plot connectivity matrix
plot_connectivity_matrix(breast_fit)

# plot connectivity interval
plot_connectivity_intervals(breast_fit) 

# plot adjacency matrix - expression
A1_plot <- plot_adjacency_matrix(breast_fit,
                      layer = "expression")

# plot adjacency matrix - spatial
A2_plot <- plot_adjacency_matrix(breast_fit,
                      layer = "spatial")
